/*
 * Smart_Probe_H2_v2.cpp  —  V2 (T5 V2.9.9k port)
 * ============================================================
 * Strictly ports IncrementalCompute.step() / compute_all() from
 * the Python Golden Reference (T5 Simulator V2.9.9k) to the
 * ATtiny3224.
 *
 * Variable mapping (Python → C++):
 *   C        → C_leaky           (leaky-integrator filtered EMF)
 *   D        → cnt_D             (up-ramp consecutive count)
 *   E        → acc_E             (up-ramp intensity accumulator)
 *   FF       → cnt_F             (down-ramp consecutive count)
 *   G        → acc_G             (down-ramp intensity accumulator)
 *   H        → h_vote            (direction vote this sample)
 *   II       → II / II_prev      (running direction indicator)
 *   J        → J_sd              (short-window SD over last 6 samples)
 *   K        → K_stab            (recovery factor from stab_rec table)
 *   L        → daughter_baseline (daughter baseline)
 *   MB       → mother_baseline   (mother / floor baseline)
 *   M        → M_delta           (C_leaky - daughter_baseline)
 *   N        → N_accum           (bulk-change accumulator)
 *   O        → O_roc             (ROC counter)
 *   P (Pv)   → P_clip            (locked N at cap)
 *   Q        → Q_ppm             (fast-path PPM via calib)
 *   R        → R_ppm             (analytical-path PPM via calib_analytical)
 *   S        → S_ppm = max(Q,R)  (display PPM)
 *   RC       → rec_pct           (recovery %)
 *
 * Warmup states:
 *   'waiting'             → WARMUP_WAITING
 *   'sd_ok_proxfail'      → WARMUP_PROX_FAIL
 *   'ready_for_tare'      → WARMUP_READY_TARE
 *   'running'             → WARMUP_RUNNING
 *
 * OR states (Python → C++ enum):
 *   'normal'        → OR_NORMAL
 *   'overrange'     → OR_OVERRANGE
 *   'waiting_drop'  → OR_WAIT_DROP
 *   'stable'        → OR_STABLE
 *
 * 8-Column UART output (space-separated, CRLF):
 *  [1] RefR         – reference-subtracted value (Reference_Set_Value)
 *  [2] EMF          – raw sensor voltage in mV (3 decimal places)
 *  [3] DispPPM      – final display PPM = max(Q,R) (integer)
 *  [4] Type         – "F" if Q >= R (fast dominant), "A" if R > Q
 *  [5] H2_Flag      – "AIR", "UP", "DOWN", or "REC"
 *  [6] Rec_Pct      – recovery % 0-100 integer
 *  [7] OR_Status    – "NORMAL", "OVERRANGE", "WAIT_DROP", "PRESS_TARE"
 *  [8] Warmup_Status– 0=Init, 1=Unstable/High-SD, 2=Prox-Fail,
 *                      3=Stable/Wait-Tare, 4=Done
 *
 * Commands:
 *  *start#               – begin output
 *  *TEAR#                – full state reset (_full_reset_state equiv)
 *  *IGNORE_PROX#         – bypass proximity check and seed baseline
 *  *RF<7-digit>#         – set reference value
 *  *T<4-digit><2-digit># – set filter limit+offset
 *  *CAL#                 – master reset (same as TEAR but announces OK_CAL)
 *  *SET <KEY> <value>#   – set parameter
 *  *SET CAL <i> <mv> <ppm>#      – edit fast calib table entry
 *  *SET ANCAL <i> <mv> <ppm>#    – edit analytical calib table entry
 *  *GET PARAMS#          – dump all params + both calibration tables
 *
 * EEPROM layout (ATtiny3224 = 256 bytes, 0x00–0xFF):
 *  0x00–0x05  : (reserved legacy / unused)
 *  0x06–0x08  : limit (3 bytes, original)
 *  0x09       : fast-calib magic  0xA5
 *  0x0A–0x51  : fast calib  9 × 8 bytes (p_mv float + ppm long)
 *  0x52       : analytical-calib magic  0xA5
 *  0x53–0x9A  : analytical calib  9 × 8 bytes
 *  0x9B–0x9D  : (gap)
 *  0x9E–0xA0  : mother_baseline float (3 bytes via ee_write_float24)
 *  0xA1       : mother_baseline magic  0xB3
 *  0x96–0x98  : offset_value (3 bytes, original = 150-152 decimal → 0x96-0x98)
 *  0xDC–0xDE  : Reference_Set_Value (3 bytes, original = 220-222 decimal → 0xDC-0xDE)
 *
 * EEPROM summary:
 *   fast    calib: magic@0x09, data@0x0A–0x51  (72 bytes for 9 entries)
 *   analyt  calib: magic@0x52, data@0x53–0x9A  (72 bytes for 9 entries)
 *   mother  BL:    float@0x9E–0xA1, magic@0xA2
 */

